column42: ACETIC ACID SOLUTION, NOT LESS THAN 50 PERCENT BUT NOT MORE THAN 80 PERCENT ACID, BY MASS
column168: ON MARCH 4, 1987, ONE OF OUR DELIVERY TRUCKS DRIVEN BY JAMES SIMMS WAS TRAVELING SOUTH ON I-285 SOUTH NEAR THE WAHSINGTON ROAD EXIT.  HE WAS FLAGG ED OVER BY ANOTHER TRUCKER WHO WAS FOLLOWING THE MAYO TRUCK. THE DRIVER STOPPED AND NOTICED A 275 GALLON PLASTIC TOTE TANK CONTAINING 84 %  ACETIC ACID WAS LEAKING.  THE SIDE WALL OF THE TANK NEAR THE TOP HAD CRACKED OPEN AND APPROXIMATELY 40 GALLONS OF MATERIAL WAS SPILLED. THE DRIVER CALLED THE MAYO CHEMICAL PLANT AND OUR EMERGENCY RESPONSE TEAM W AS DISPACHTED WITH A SPARE TANK, SODA ASH FOR NEUTRALIZATION, ABSORBENT PILLOWS FOR ABSORBING THE SPILL, AND MISCELLANEOUS SAFETY EQUIPMENT SUCH AS HATS, GOGGLES, GLOVES, PVC SUITS, SELF CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS, EYE WASHES, ETC.  ALSO THE FULTON COUNTY FIRE DEPARTMENT WAS DISPATCHED TO THE SCENE. UPON ARRIVAL THE RESPONSE TEAM IMMEDIATLY BEGAN ABSOBING THE SPILL AND NEUT RALIZING IT WITH SODA ASH.  THE MATERIAL WAS THEN TRANSFERED TO THE EMPTY T ANK FOR TRANSPORT BACK TO OUR PLANT.  THE AREA WAS THEN FLUSHED WITH WATER BY THE FIRE DEPARTMENT. THE SOIL PH WAS CHECKED BY MR. TIM CASH OF THE GEORGIA DEPARTMENT OF NATUR- AL RESOURCES AND WAS FOUND TO BE 6.7 WHICH WAS WITHIN REQUIRED PARAMETERS. ACCORDING TO MR. CASH, NO FURTHER TREATMENT OR DISPOSAL AT THE SITE WILL BE REQUIRED. THE WASTE MATERIALS WERE COLLECTED AND RETURNED TO THE PLANT FOR PROPER PACKAGING AND SHIPMENT TO A HAZARDOUS WASTE DISPOSAL SITE. THE TOTE TANK WAS MANUFACTURED BY CLAWSON TANK COMPANY OF CLARKSON, MICHIGAN WHICH IS APPROVED TO HANDLE CORROSIVES SUCH AS THIS PRODUCT. THE MANUFACTURER HAS BEEN NOTIFIED OF THIS INCIDENT AND AN INVESTIGATION IS UNDERWAY TO ASCER- TAIN THE FAILURE OF THIS TANK. UNTIL SUCH INVESTIGATION IS COMPLETE, NO SHIPMENTS WILL BE MADE WITH THIS CONTAINER.

WHILE SWITCHING THIS TANK CAR, A SWITCHMAN WAS SPLASHED.INSPECTION REVEALED A DEFECTIVE FILL HOLE GASKET.  SHIPPER SENT A RESPONSE TEAM WHO REPLACED GASKET WITH RAILROAD'S SPECIAL AGENT-HAZARDOUSMATERIALS. SWITCHMAN ONLY SUFFERED MINOR BURNS ABOUT FACE AND UPPER BODY AS HE PROMPTLY SHOWERED AFTER BIENG SPLASHED.
